section.section:
A pre-need contract shall contain:
The name of each party to the contract and, if the beneficiary is an individual other than the buyer, the name of the beneficiary of the contract;
A description of any service or merchandise to be provided under the pre-need contract;
A disclosure statement that clearly:
The total price of the services and merchandise agreed on; and
The method of payment.

A pre-need contract is ended and a seller shall refund to a buyer all payments and interest held for the buyer if:
The buyer or the legal representative of the buyer demands in writing a refund of all payments made;
The business of the seller is discontinued or sold;
The seller is unable to perform under the terms and conditions of the pre-need contract; or
The buyer fails to pay the entire contract price before the death of the beneficiary, and the seller considers the pre-need contract void.
